title: Bracknell (North) bike routes
name: Bracknell (North) bike routes
description:
A Map by Jhbiketowork

Please add your comments on the different routes!

properties.name: A3095 Maidenhead Road
properties.description: Posted by Jhbiketowork

properties.name: Bishop's lane
properties.description: Posted by Vademecum Useful back-road to avoid A330. Single-track road, not quite a byway

properties.name: Bottle Lane
properties.description: Posted by JhbiketoworkFor a minor road this gets a lot of traffic, but it is reasonable wide. Can be icy in frost.

properties.name: Bridleway
properties.description: Posted by Jhbiketowork  A much poorer ride than Hog Oak Lane.

properties.name: Cabbage Hill
properties.description: Posted by JhbiketoworkA steep hill be the standards of East Berkshire, and there\'s a lot of traffic. But it has a very good surface and it is reasonable wide/

properties.name: Foliejon Park
properties.description: Posted by VademecumThis seemed like a good way of avoiding the slog up Hawthorn Hill travelling South from Fifield. Last year two huge green cast-iron gates were erected. Shame.

properties.name: Hawthorn Hill
properties.description: Posted by VademecumAs I\'m sure we\'re all aware, a terrifying stretch of road - from 08.00 to 09.00 is particularly hairy

properties.name: Hazelwood Lane (North)
properties.description: Posted by JhbiketoworkBridleway. OK on a road bike in summer as far as Buckle Lane. Mountain bike better to Gough\'s Barn Lane!

properties.name: Hazelwood Lane (South)
properties.description: Posted by JhbiketoworkBridleway - loose surface so best on a mountain bike.

properties.name: Hogoak Lane (North)
properties.description: Posted by VademecumNorthern terminus of the Hawthorn Hill \'bypass\'. Dirt byway with a reasonable amount of hardcore or gravel in places.

properties.name: Hogoak lane
properties.description: Posted by JhbiketoworkGood quality bridle-way. OK on a road bike if it is dry!

properties.name: Monk's Alley bridleways
properties.description: Posted by Jhbiketowork

properties.name: Nuptown/Hawthorn Lane
properties.description: Posted by Vademecum Hawthorne Lane is a continuation of the Hogoak Lane byway and is well maintained. A faster route is to follow Nuptown lane and take a short ride up the A330 to Weller\'s Lane

properties.name: Off-road to Holyport
properties.description: Posted by Jhbiketowork  Another good bridleway alternative to the A330.

properties.name: Osborne Lane
properties.description: Posted by JhbiketoworkA bit twisty, but much less traffic than the A3095.

properties.name: Priory Lane
properties.description: Posted by JhbiketoworkNow a dead end thanks to the Bracknell Northern Relief Road, so little traffic and you can get through to the Warfield Road (A3095) in Bracknell.

properties.name: Ryehurst Lane
properties.description: Posted by JhbiketoworkA fairly quiet country lane. The stream floods the road but there\'s a footbridge.

properties.name: Summerleaze Bridge
properties.description: Posted by VademecumThe most practical Thames crossing between Eton and Maidenhead

properties.name: Weller's Lane
properties.description: Posted by JhbiketoworkWhy cycle on the A3095 when you can cycle on this much quieter country lane?

properties.name: Winkfield Lane (North)
properties.description: Posted by Vademecum A useful alternative route to Hawthorn Hill when travelling South from Fifield. Gentler gradients and fewer cars
